name: Flaaffy
flavorText: As a result of storing too much electricity, it developed patches where even downy wool won't grow.

name: Lucario ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Ampharos ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Cyclizar ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Pelipper
flavorText: It is a flying transporter that carries small Pokémon in its beak. It bobs on the waves to rest its wings.

name: Baxcalibur
flavorText: This Pokémon blasts cryogenic air out from its mouth. This air can instantly freeze even liquid-hot lava.

name: Tinkaton
flavorText: This intelligent Pokémon has a very daring disposition. It knocks rocks into the sky with its hammer, aiming for flying Corviknight.

name: Murkrow
flavorText: Feared and loathed by many, it is believed to bring misfortune to all those who see it at night.

name: Smoliv
flavorText: It protects itself from enemies by emitting oil from the fruit on its head. This oil is bitter and astringent enough to make someone flinch.

name: Tinkatink
flavorText: It swings its handmade hammer around to protect itself, but the hammer is often stolen by Pokémon that eat metal.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: Pikachu seems excited to be going on an adventure, and so do its new pals, from attention-seeking Sprigatito to laid-back Fuecoco and tidy Quaxly.

name: Koraidon ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Growlithe
flavorText: It's very friendly and faithful to people. It will try to repel enemies by barking and biting.

name: Varoom
flavorText: It is said that this Pokémon was born when an unknown poison Pokémon entered and inspirited an engine left at a scrap-processing factory.

name: Miraidon ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Surskit
flavorText: They usually live on ponds, but after an evening shower, they may appear on puddles in towns.

name: Gloom
flavorText: What appears to be drool is actually sweet honey. It is very sticky and clings stubbornly if touched.

name: Oddish
flavorText: During the day, it stays in the cold underground to avoid the sun. It grows by bathing in moonlight.

name: Phantump
flavorText: With a voice like a human child's, it cries out to lure adults deep into the forest, getting them lost among the trees.

name: Steenee
flavorText: Steenee spreads a sweet scent that makes others feel invigorated. This same scent is popular for antiperspirants.

name: Charmeleon
flavorText: If it becomes agitated during battle, it spouts intense flames, incinerating its surroundings.

name: Camerupt
flavorText: It lives in the crater of a volcano. It is well known that the humps on its back erupt every 10 years.

name: Victini ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Darmanitan
flavorText: This Pokémon's power level rises along with the temperature of its fire, which can reach 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Scyther
flavorText: It slashes through grass with its sharp scythes, moving too fast for the human eye to track.

name: Foongus
flavorText: There is a theory that the developer of the modern-day Poké Ball really liked Foongus, but this has not been confirmed.

name: Capsakid
flavorText: The more sunlight this Pokémon bathes in, the more spicy chemicals are produced by its body, and thus the spicier its moves become.

name: Scovillain
flavorText: The red head converts spicy chemicals into fire energy and blasts the surrounding area with a super spicy stream of flame.

name: Numel
flavorText: Magma of almost 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit courses through its body. When it grows cold, the magma hardens and slows it.

name: Darumaka
flavorText: This popular symbol of good fortune will never fall over in its sleep, no matter how it's pushed or pulled.

name: Combee
flavorText: At night, Combee sleep in a group of about a hundred, packed closely together in a lump.

name: Bellossom
flavorText: Bellossom gather at times and appear to dance. They say that the dance is a ritual to summon the sun.

name: Shuckle
flavorText: The berries stored in its vaselike shell eventually become a thick, pulpy juice.

name: Masquerain
flavorText: It flaps its four wings to hover and fly freely in any direction—to and fro and sideways.

name: Amoonguss
flavorText: Be wary of the poisonous spores it releases. Mushrooms resembling Amoonguss's caps will grow out of anywhere the spores touch.

name: Trevenant
flavorText: Small roots that extend from the tips of this Pokémon's feet can tie into the trees of the forest and give Trevenant control over them.

name: Decidueye ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Bounsweet
flavorText: Its sweat is sweet, like syrup made from boiled-down fruit. Because of this, Bounsweet was highly valued in the past, when sweeteners were scarce.

name: Tsareena
flavorText: This Pokémon is proud and aggressive. However, it is said that a Tsareena will instantly become calm if someone touches the crown on its calyx.

name: Smoliv
flavorText: It protects itself from enemies by emitting oil from the fruit on its head. This oil is bitter and astringent enough to make someone flinch.

name: Dolliv
flavorText: Dolliv shares its tasty, fresh-scented oil with others. This species has coexisted with humans since times long gone.

name: Toedscruel ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Vulpix
flavorText: As each tail grows, its fur becomes more lustrous. When held, it feels slightly warm.

name: Rowlet
flavorText: It feels relaxed in tight, dark places and has been known to use its Trainer's pocket or bag as a nest.

name: Dartrix
flavorText: Supremely sensitive to the presence of others, it can detect opponents standing behind it, flinging its sharp feathers to take them out.

name: Arboliva
flavorText: This calm Pokémon is very compassionate. It will share its delicious, nutrient-rich oil with weakened Pokémon.

name: Capsakid
flavorText: The more sunlight this Pokémon bathes in, the more spicy chemicals are produced by its body, and thus the spicier its moves become.

name: Charmander
flavorText: From the time it is born, a flame burns at the tip of its tail. Its life would end if the flame were to go out.

name: Ninetales
flavorText: Very smart and very vengeful. Grabbing one of its many tails could result in a 1,000-year curse.

name: Entei
flavorText: It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.

name: Litwick
flavorText: The younger the life this Pokémon absorbs, the brighter and eerier the flame on its head burns.

name: Eiscue ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.","Tera: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's)."]

name: Lapras
flavorText: Crossing icy seas is no issue for this cold-resistant Pokémon. Its smooth skin is a little cool to the touch.

name: Buizel
flavorText: It spins its two tails like a screw to propel itself through water. The tails also slice clinging seaweed.

name: Beartic
flavorText: It is a ferocious, carnivorous Pokémon. Once it captures its prey, it will breathe cold air onto the prey to freeze and preserve it.

name: Wiglett
flavorText: This Pokémon can pick up the scent of a Veluza just over 65 feet away and will hide itself in the sand.

name: Finizen
flavorText: It likes playing with others of its kind using the water ring on its tail. It uses ultrasonic waves to sense the emotions of other living creatures.

name: Palafin
flavorText: This Pokémon's ancient genes have awakened. It is now so extraordinarily strong that it can easily lift a cruise ship with one fin.

name: Magneton
flavorText: Three Magnemite are linked by a strong magnetic force. Earaches will occur if you get too close.

name: Magnezone
flavorText: As it zooms through the sky, this Pokémon seems to be receiving signals of unknown origin while transmitting signals of unknown purpose.

name: Thundurus
flavorText: As it flies around, it shoots lightning all over the place and causes forest fires. It is therefore disliked.

name: Toxel
flavorText: It has no problem drinking dirty water. An organ inside Toxel's body filters such water into a poisonous liquid that is harmless to Toxel.

name: Tadbulb
flavorText: Tadbulb shakes its tail to generate electricity. If it senses danger, it will make its head blink on and off to alert its allies.

name: Clefable ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Espeon
flavorText: The tip of its forked tail quivers when it is predicting its opponent's next move.

name: Granbull
flavorText: Although it's popular with young people, Granbull is timid and sensitive, so it's totally incompetent as a watchdog.

name: Baltoy
flavorText: It was discovered in ancient ruins. While moving, it constantly spins. It stands on one foot even when asleep.

name: Claydol
flavorText: It appears to have been born from clay dolls made by ancient people. It uses telekinesis to float and move.

name: Vespiquen ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.","Tera: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's)."]

name: Sinistea
flavorText: The soul of someone who died alone possessed some leftover tea. This Pokémon appears in hotels and houses.

name: Diglett
flavorText: It lives about one yard underground, where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears aboveground.

name: Barboach
flavorText: Its two whiskers provide a sensitive radar. Even in muddy waters, it can detect its prey's location.

name: Whiscash
flavorText: It is extremely protective of its territory. If any foe approaches, it attacks using vicious tremors.

name: Crabrawler
flavorText: This Pokémon punches trees and eats the berries that drop down, training itself and getting food at the same time.

name: Crabominable
flavorText: The detached pincers of these Pokémon are delicious. Some Trainers bring Lechonk into the mountains just to search for them.

name: Rockruff
flavorText: This Pokémon is very friendly when it's young. Its disposition becomes vicious once it matures, but it never forgets the kindness of its master.

name: Lycanroc
flavorText: This Pokémon uses its rocky mane to slash any who approach. It will even disobey its Trainer if it dislikes the orders it was given.

name: Glimmet
flavorText: It absorbs nutrients from cave walls. The petals it wears are made of crystallized poison.

name: Paldean Wooper
flavorText: After losing a territorial struggle, Wooper began living on land. The Pokémon changed over time, developing a poisonous film to protect its body.

name: Paldean Clodsire
flavorText: When attacked, this Pokémon will retaliate by sticking thick spines out from its body. It's a risky move that puts everything on the line.

name: Heatmor
flavorText: A flame serves as its tongue, melting through the hard shell of Durant so that Heatmor can devour their insides.

name: Floatzel
flavorText: With its flotation sac inflated, it can carry people on its back. It deflates the sac before it dives.

name: Tympole
flavorText: It uses sound waves to communicate with others of its kind. People and other Pokémon species can't hear its cries of warning.

name: Cubchoo
flavorText: Many of this species can be found along the shorelines of cold regions. If a Cubchoo lacks dangling snot, there's a chance it is sick.

name: Cryogonal
flavorText: Cryogonal appear during cold seasons. It is said that people and Pokémon who die on snowy mountains are reborn into these Pokémon.

name: Magnemite
flavorText: The electromagnetic waves emitted by the units at the sides of its head expel antigravity, which allows it to float.

name: Tyranitar ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.","Tera: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's)."]

name: Tynamo
flavorText: While one alone doesn't have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.

name: Eelektrik
flavorText: They coil around foes and shock them with electricity-generating organs that seem simply to be circular patterns.

name: Eelektross
flavorText: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

name: Tadbulb
flavorText: Tadbulb shakes its tail to generate electricity. If it senses danger, it will make its head blink on and off to alert its allies.

name: Cleffa
flavorText: Because of its unusual, starlike silhouette, people believe that it came here on a meteor.

name: Clefairy
flavorText: Its adorable behavior and cry make it highly popular. However, this cute Pokémon is rarely found.

name: Togepi
flavorText: It is considered to be a symbol of good luck. Its shell is said to be filled with happiness.

name: Togekiss
flavorText: Known as a bringer of blessings, it's been depicted on good-luck charms since ancient times.

name: Snubbull
flavorText: In contrast to its appearance, it's quite timid. When playing with other puppy Pokémon, it sometimes gets bullied.

name: Lunatone
flavorText: It was discovered at the site of a meteor strike 40 years ago. Its stare can lull its foes to sleep.

name: Greavard
flavorText: It is said that a dog Pokémon that died in the wild without ever interacting with a human was reborn as this Pokémon.

name: Larvitar
flavorText: Born deep underground, this Pokémon becomes a pupa after eating enough dirt to make a mountain.

name: Pupitar
flavorText: This pupa flies around wildly by venting with great force the gas pressurized inside its body.

name: Toedscruel
flavorText: These Pokémon gather into groups and form colonies deep within forests. They absolutely hate it when strangers approach.

name: Koraidon ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Lampent
flavorText: It lurks in cities, pretending to be a lamp. Once it finds someone whose death is near, it will trail quietly after them.

name: Volcarona
flavorText: Its burning body causes it to be unpopular in hot parts of the world, but in cold ones, Volcarona is revered as an embodiment of the sun.

name: Armarouge
flavorText: Armarouge evolved through the use of a set of armor that belonged to a distinguished warrior. This Pokémon is incredibly loyal.

name: Sharpedo
flavorText: This Pokémon is known as the Bully of the Sea. Any ship entering the waters Sharpedo calls home will be attacked—no exceptions.

name: Seismitoad
flavorText: This Pokémon is popular among the elderly, who say the vibrations of its lumps are great for massages.

name: Toxtricity
flavorText: Many youths admire the way this Pokémon listlessly picks fights and keeps its cool no matter what opponent it faces.

name: Bellibolt
flavorText: When this Pokémon expands and contracts its wobbly body, the belly-button dynamo in its stomach produces a huge amount of electricity.

name: Mawile
flavorText: It chomps with its gaping mouth. Its huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed.

name: Spoink
flavorText: Spoink will die if it stops bouncing. The pearl on its head amplifies its psychic powers.

name: Greavard
flavorText: It is said that a dog Pokémon that died in the wild without ever interacting with a human was reborn as this Pokémon.

name: Nosepass
flavorText: It hunts without twitching a muscle by pulling in its prey with powerful magnetism. But sometimes it pulls natural enemies in close.

name: Bonsly
flavorText: In order to adjust the level of fluids in its body, it exudes water from its eyes. This makes it appear to be crying.

name: Drilbur
flavorText: It's a digger, using its claws to burrow through the ground. It causes damage to vegetable crops, so many farmers have little love for it.

name: Stunfisk
flavorText: For some reason, this Pokémon smiles slightly when it emits a strong electric current from the yellow markings on its body.

name: Klawf ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Paldean Clodsire
flavorText: When attacked, this Pokémon will retaliate by sticking thick spines out from its body. It's a risky move that puts everything on the line.

name: Chandelure
flavorText: In homes illuminated by Chandelure instead of lights, funerals were a constant occurrence—or so it's said.

name: Larvesta
flavorText: This Pokémon was called the Larva That Stole the Sun. The fire Larvesta spouts from its horns can cut right through a sheet of iron.

name: Charcadet
flavorText: Burnt charcoal came to life and became a Pokémon. Possessing a fiery fighting spirit, Charcadet will battle even tough opponents.

name: Carvanha
flavorText: These Pokémon have sharp fangs and powerful jaws. Sailors avoid Carvanha dens at all costs.

name: Palpitoad
flavorText: On occasion, their cries are sublimely pleasing to the ear. Palpitoad with larger lumps on their bodies can sing with a wider range of sounds.

name: Froakie
flavorText: It protects its skin by covering its body in delicate bubbles. Beneath its happy-go-lucky air, it keeps a watchful eye on its surroundings.

name: Frogadier
flavorText: Its swiftness is unparalleled. It can scale a tower of more than 600 metres in a minute's time.

name: Wugtrio
flavorText: It has a vicious temperament, contrary to what its appearance may suggest. It wraps its long bodies around prey, then drags the prey into its den.

name: Finizen
flavorText: It likes playing with others of its kind using the water ring on its tail. It uses ultrasonic waves to sense the emotions of other living creatures.

name: Pawmot ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Tadbulb
flavorText: Tadbulb shakes its tail to generate electricity. If it senses danger, it will make its head blink on and off to alert its allies.

name: Bellibolt
flavorText: When this Pokémon expands and contracts its wobbly body, the belly-button dynamo in its stomach produces a huge amount of electricity.

name: Miraidon ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Togetic
flavorText: It grows dispirited if it is not with kind people. It can float in midair without moving its wings.

name: Grumpig
flavorText: It can perform odd dance steps to influence foes. Its style of dancing became hugely popular overseas.

name: Solrock
flavorText: Solar energy is the source of its power, so it is strong during the daytime. When it spins, its body shines.

name: Polteageist
flavorText: The tea that composes Polteageist's body has a distinct and enjoyable flavor. Drinking too much, however, can be fatal.

name: Houndstone
flavorText: Houndstone spends most of its time sleeping in graveyards. Among all the dog Pokémon, this one is most loyal to its master.

name: Houndstone ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Dugtrio
flavorText: Its three heads bob separately up and down to loosen the soil nearby, making it easier for it to burrow.

name: Diggersby
flavorText: The fur on its belly retains heat exceptionally well. People used to make heavy winter clothing from fur shed by this Pokémon.

name: Toedscool
flavorText: Toedscool lives in muggy forests. The flaps that fall from its body are chewy and very delicious.

name: Glimmet
flavorText: It absorbs nutrients from cave walls. The petals it wears are made of crystallized poison.

name: Glimmora ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Charizard ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.","Tera: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's)."]

name: Paldean Wooper
flavorText: After losing a territorial struggle, Wooper began living on land. The Pokémon changed over time, developing a poisonous film to protect its body.

name: Houndour
flavorText: It is smart enough to hunt in packs. It uses a variety of cries for communicating with others.

name: Houndour
flavorText: It is smart enough to hunt in packs. It uses a variety of cries for communicating with others.

name: Houndoom
flavorText: If you are burned by the flames it shoots from its mouth, the pain will never go away.

name: Scizor
flavorText: This Pokémon's pincers, which contain steel, can crush any hard object they get ahold of into bits.

name: Darkrai
flavorText: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.

name: Skarmory
flavorText: People fashion swords from Skarmory's shed feathers, so this Pokémon is a popular element in heraldic designs.

name: Salandit
flavorText: It taunts its prey and lures them into narrow, rocky areas where it then sprays them with toxic gas to make them dizzy and take them down.

name: Togedemaru
flavorText: When it's in trouble, it curls up into a ball, makes its fur spikes stand on end, and then discharges electricity indiscriminately.

name: Bronzor
flavorText: Ancient people believed that the pattern on Bronzor's back contained a mysterious power.

name: Meltan
flavorText: They live as a group, but when the time comes, one strong Meltan will absorb all the others and evolve.

name: Bronzong
flavorText: In ages past, this Pokémon was revered as a bringer of rain. It was found buried in the ground.

name: Melmetal ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Bisharp
flavorText: This Pokémon commands a group of several Pawniard. Groups that are defeated in territorial disputes are absorbed by the winning side.

name: Dragonair
flavorText: They say that if it emits an aura from its whole body, the weather will begin to change instantly.

name: Kingambit
flavorText: Only a Bisharp that stands above all others in its vast army can evolve into Kingambit.

name: Pidgey
flavorText: It is docile and prefers to avoid conflict. If disturbed, however, it can ferociously strike back.

name: Inkay
flavorText: By exposing foes to the blinking of its luminescent spots, Inkay demoralizes them, and then it seizes the chance to flee.

name: Umbreon
flavorText: When exposed to the moon's aura, the rings on its body glow faintly and it gains a mysterious power.

name: Malamar
flavorText: It's said that Malamar's hypnotic powers played a role in certain history-changing events.

name: Salazzle
flavorText: Salazzle makes its opponents light-headed with poisonous gas, then captivates them with alluring movements to turn them into loyal servants.

name: Mawile
flavorText: It chomps with its gaping mouth. Its huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed.

name: Excadrill
flavorText: Known as the Drill King, this Pokémon can tunnel through the terrain at speeds of over 90 mph.

name: Dratini
flavorText: It sheds many layers of skin as it grows larger. During this process, it is protected by a rapid waterfall.

name: Dragonite ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.","Tera: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's)."]

name: Drampa
flavorText: Drampa is a kind and friendly Pokémon—up until it's angered. When that happens, it stirs up a gale and flattens everything around.

name: Houndoom ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Absol ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Probopass
flavorText: It uses three small units to catch prey and battle enemies. The main body mostly just gives orders.

name: Pawniard
flavorText: Pawniard will fearlessly challenge even powerful foes. In a pinch, it will cling to opponents and pierce them with the blades all over its body.

name: Varoom
flavorText: It is said that this Pokémon was born when an unknown poison Pokémon entered and inspirited an engine left at a scrap-processing factory.

name: Varoom
flavorText: It is said that this Pokémon was born when an unknown poison Pokémon entered and inspirited an engine left at a scrap-processing factory.

name: Revavroom ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Altaria
flavorText: If it bonds with a person, it will gently envelop the friend with its soft wings, then hum.

name: Pidgeot ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Kangaskhan
flavorText: There are records of a lost human child being raised by a childless Kangaskhan.

name: Pidgeotto
flavorText: Very protective of its sprawling territorial area, this Pokémon will fiercely peck at any intruder.

name: Eevee
flavorText: Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.

name: Linoone
flavorText: It uses its explosive speed and razor-sharp claws to bring down prey. Running along winding paths is not its strong suit.

name: Zigzagoon
flavorText: A Pokémon with abundant curiosity. It shows an interest in everything, so it always zigzags.

name: Swablu
flavorText: It constantly grooms its cotton-like wings. It takes a shower to clean itself if it becomes dirty.

name: Lillipup
flavorText: This Pokémon is far brighter than the average child, and Lillipup won't forget the love it receives or any abuse it suffers.

name: Bouffalant
flavorText: These Pokémon live in herds of about 20 individuals. Bouffalant that betray the herd will lose the hair on their heads for some reason.

name: Yungoos
flavorText: Its stomach fills most of its torso. It wanders the same path every day, searching for fresh food.

name: Greedent ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.","Tera: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's)."]

name: Lechonk
flavorText: It searches for food all day. It possesses a keen sense of smell but doesn't use it for anything other than foraging.

name: Geeta
rules: ["Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Energy cards and attach them to 1 of your Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck. During this turn, your Pokémon can't attack. (This includes Pokémon that come into play this turn.)","You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn."]

name: Letter of Encouragement
rules: ["You can use this card only if any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out during your opponent's last turn.","Search your deck for up to 3 Basic Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.","You may play any number of Item cards during your turn."]

name: Bunnelby
flavorText: It's very sensitive to danger. The sound of Corviknight's flapping will have Bunnelby digging a hole to hide underground in moments.

name: Gumshoos
flavorText: Once it finds signs of prey, it will patiently stake out the location, waiting until the sun goes down.

name: Lechonk
flavorText: It searches for food all day. It possesses a keen sense of smell but doesn't use it for anything other than foraging.

name: Ortega

name: Stoutland
flavorText: Stoutland is immensely proud of its impressive moustache. It's said that moustache length is what determines social standing among this species.

name: Audino
flavorText: This Pokémon has a kind heart. By touching with its feelers, Audino can gauge other creatures' feelings and physical conditions.

name: Oinkologne
flavorText: This Pokémon sends a flowerlike scent wafting about. Well-developed muscles in its legs allow it to leap more than 16 feet with no trouble at all.

name: Flamigo
flavorText: This Pokémon apparently ties the base of its neck into a knot so that the energy stored in its belly does not escape from its beak.

name: Arven
rules: ["Search your deck for an Item card and a Pokémon Tool card, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.","You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn."]

name: Brassius
rules: ["Count the cards in your hand, shuffle those cards into your deck, then draw that many cards plus 1.","You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn."]

name: Herdier
flavorText: The black fur that covers this Pokémon's body is dense and springy. Even sharp fangs bounce right off.

name: Skwovet
flavorText: It stores berries in its cheeks. When there are no berries to be found, Skwovet will stuff pebbles into its cheeks to stave off its cravings.

name: Oinkologne

A Stadium with the same name can't be played."]

name: Pidgeotto
flavorText: Very protective of its sprawling territorial area, this Pokémon will fiercely peck at any intruder.

name: Ryme
rules: ["Draw 3 cards. Switch out your opponent's Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.)","You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn."]

name: Lechonk
flavorText: It searches for food all day. It possesses a keen sense of smell but doesn't use it for anything other than foraging.

name: Town Store
rules: ["Once during each player's turn, that player may search their deck for a Pokémon Tool card, reveal it, and put it into their hand. Then, that player shuffles their deck.","You may play only 1 Stadium card during your turn. Put it next to the Active Spot, and discard it if another Stadium comes into play. A Stadium with the same name can't be played."]

name: Tyranitar ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.","Tera: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's)."]

name: Gloom
flavorText: What appears to be drool is actually sweet honey. It is very sticky and clings stubbornly if touched.

name: Absol ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Bellibolt
flavorText: When this Pokémon expands and contracts its wobbly body, the belly-button dynamo in its stomach produces a huge amount of electricity.

name: Poppy
rules: ["Move up to 2 Energy from 1 of your Pokémon to another of your Pokémon.","You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn."]

name: Scizor
flavorText: This Pokémon's pincers, which contain steel, can crush any hard object they get ahold of into bits.

name: Charizard ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.","Tera: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's)."]

name: Eiscue ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.","Tera: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's)."]

name: Revavroom ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Geeta
rules: ["Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Energy cards and attach them to 1 of your Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck. During this turn, your Pokémon can't attack. (This includes Pokémon that come into play this turn.)","You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn."]

name: Ortega
rules: ["Your opponent reveals their hand, and you choose a card you find there and put it on the bottom of their deck. If you put a card on the bottom of your opponent's deck in this way, your opponent may draw a card.","You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn."]

name: Revavroom ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Poppy
rules: ["Move up to 2 Energy from 1 of your Pokémon to another of your Pokémon.","You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn."]

name: Chien-Pao ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Tinkaton ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Annihilape ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Palafin
flavorText: This Pokémon's ancient genes have awakened. It is now so extraordinarily strong that it can easily lift a cruise ship with one fin.

name: Cleffa
flavorText: Because of its unusual, starlike silhouette, people believe that it came here on a meteor.

name: Togekiss
flavorText: Known as a bringer of blessings, it's been depicted on good-luck charms since ancient times.

name: Mawile
flavorText: It chomps with its gaping mouth. Its huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed.

name: Pawmi
flavorText: It has underdeveloped electric sacs on its cheeks. These sacs can produce electricity only if Pawmi rubs them furiously with the pads on its forepaws.

name: Paldean Wooper
flavorText: After losing a territorial struggle, Wooper began living on land. The Pokémon changed over time, developing a poisonous film to protect its body.

name: Houndstone
flavorText: Houndstone spends most of its time sleeping in graveyards. Among all the dog Pokémon, this one is most loyal to its master.

name: Eevee
flavorText: Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.

name: Charmander
flavorText: From the time it is born, a flame burns at the tip of its tail. Its life would end if the flame were to go out.

name: Paradise Resort
rules: ["The Retreat Cost of each Psyduck in play (both yours and your opponent's) is Colorless less.","You may play only 1 Stadium card during your turn. Put it next to the Active Spot, and discard it if another Stadium comes into play. A Stadium with the same name can't be played."]

name: Ivysaur
flavorText: Exposure to sunlight adds to its strength. Sunlight also makes the bud on its back grow larger.

name: Bulbasaur
flavorText: While it is young, it uses the nutrients that are stored in the seed on its back in order to grow.

name: Venusaur ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Squirtle
flavorText: When it feels threatened, it draws its limbs inside its shell and sprays water from its mouth.

name: Rattata
flavorText: This Pokémon is common but hazardous. Its sharp incisors can easily cut right through hard wood.

name: Wartortle
flavorText: It cleverly controls its furry ears and tail to maintain its balance while swimming.

name: Ekans
flavorText: The eggs of bird Pokémon are its favorite food. It swallows eggs whole, so sometimes an egg gets stuck, and Ekans faints.

name: Blastoise ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Arbok ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Butterfree
flavorText: It collects honey every day. It rubs honey onto the hairs on its legs to carry it back to its nest.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.

name: Pidgey
flavorText: It is docile and prefers to avoid conflict. If disturbed, however, it can ferociously strike back.

name: Nidoran ♀
flavorText: It uses its hard incisor teeth to crush and eat berries. The tip of a female Nidoran's horn is a bit more rounded than the tip of a male's horn.

name: Spearow
flavorText: Due to its short wings, it can't fly long distances. It wanders about restlessly and pecks at bug Pokémon.

name: Nidorino
flavorText: It's nervous and quick to act aggressively. The potency of its poison increases along with the level of adrenaline present in its body.

name: Nidorina
flavorText: If the group is threatened, these Pokémon will band together to assault enemies with a chorus of ultrasonic waves.

name: Nidoking
flavorText: Nidoking prides itself on its strength. It's forceful and spirited in battle, making use of its thick tail and diamond-crushing horn.

name: Nidoran ♂
flavorText: Small but brave, this Pokémon will hold its ground and even risk its life in battle to protect the female it's friendly with.

name: Clefairy
flavorText: Its adorable behavior and cry make it highly popular. However, this cute Pokémon is rarely found.

name: Clefable
flavorText: Their ears are sensitive enough to hear a pin drop from over a mile away, so they're usually found in quiet places.

name: Gloom
flavorText: What appears to be drool is actually sweet honey. It is very sticky and clings stubbornly if touched.

name: Vileplume
flavorText: The larger its petals, the more toxic pollen it contains. Its big head is heavy and hard to hold up.

name: Paras
flavorText: The mushrooms, known as tochukaso, are controlling the bug. Even if the bug bugs the mushrooms, they tell it to bug off.

name: Dugtrio
flavorText: Its three heads bob separately up and down to loosen the soil nearby, making it easier for it to burrow.

name: Parasect
flavorText: The bug is mostly dead, with the mushroom on its back having become the main body. If the mushroom comes off, the bug stops moving.

name: Diglett
flavorText: It lives about one yard underground, where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears aboveground.

name: Charmander
flavorText: From the time it is born, a flame burns at the tip of its tail. Its life would end if the flame were to go out.

name: Kakuna
flavorText: While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.

name: Charmeleon
flavorText: If it becomes agitated during battle, it spouts intense flames, incinerating its surroundings.

name: Charizard ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Caterpie
flavorText: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.

name: Metapod
flavorText: Even though it is encased in a sturdy shell, the body inside is tender. It can't withstand a harsh attack.

name: Weedle
flavorText: Its poison stinger is very powerful. Its bright-colored body is intended to warn off its enemies.

name: Pidgeotto
flavorText: Very protective of its sprawling territorial area, this Pokémon will fiercely peck at any intruder.

name: Pidgeot
flavorText: It spreads its gorgeous wings widely to intimidate enemies. It races through the skies at Mach-2 speed.

name: Raichu
flavorText: Its tail discharges electricity into the ground, protecting it from getting shocked.

name: Sandshrew
flavorText: It burrows into the ground to create its nest. If hard stones impede its tunneling, it uses its sharp claws to shatter them and then carries on digging.

name: Sandslash
flavorText: It climbs trees by hooking on with its sharp claws. Sandslash shares the berries it gathers, dropping them down to Sandshrew waiting below the tree.

name: Nidoqueen
flavorText: It pacifies offspring by placing them in the gaps between the spines on its back. The spines will never secrete poison while young are present.

name: Jigglypuff
flavorText: When its huge eyes waver, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.

name: Wigglytuff ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Zubat
flavorText: Zubat live in caves, down where the sun's light won't reach. In the morning, they gather together to keep each other warm as they sleep.

name: Oddish
flavorText: During the day, it stays in the cold underground to avoid the sun. It grows by bathing in moonlight.

name: Venomoth
flavorText: The wings are covered with dustlike scales. Every time it flaps its wings, it looses highly toxic dust.

name: Beedrill
flavorText: May appear in a swarm. Flies at violent speeds, all the while stabbing with the toxic stinger on its rear.

name: Raticate
flavorText: Its whiskers are essential for maintaining its balance. No matter how friendly you are, it will get angry and bite you if you touch its whiskers.

name: Fearow
flavorText: Carrying food through Fearow's territory is dangerous. It will snatch the food away from you in a flash!

name: Vulpix
flavorText: As each tail grows, its fur becomes more lustrous. When held, it feels slightly warm.

name: Ninetales ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Golbat
flavorText: Its feet are tiny, but this Pokémon walks skillfully. It sneaks up on sleeping prey before sinking in its fangs and slurping up blood.

name: Venonat
flavorText: Poison oozes from all over its body. It catches small bug Pokémon at night that are attracted by light.

name: Meowth
flavorText: All it does is sleep during the daytime. At night, it patrols its territory with its eyes aglow.

name: Persian
flavorText: Although its fur has many admirers, it is tough to raise as a pet because of its fickle meanness.

name: Arcanine
flavorText: An ancient picture scroll shows that people were captivated by its movement as it ran through prairies.

name: Psyduck
flavorText: It is constantly wracked by a headache. When the headache turns intense, it begins using mysterious powers.

name: Poliwag
flavorText: In rivers with fast-flowing water, this Pokémon will cling to a rock by using its thick lips, which act like a suction cup.

name: Poliwhirl
flavorText: This Pokémon's sweat is a slimy mucus. When captured, Poliwhirl can slither from its enemies' grasp and escape.

name: Victreebel
flavorText: Once ingested into this Pokémon's body, even the hardest object will melt into nothing.

name: Rapidash
flavorText: The fastest runner becomes the leader, and it decides the herd's pace and direction of travel.

name: Magneton
flavorText: Three Magnemite are linked by a strong magnetic force. Earaches will occur if you get too close.

name: Dodrio
flavorText: An odd species that is rarely found. The three heads respectively represent joy, sadness, and anger.

name: Gastly
flavorText: It wraps its opponent in its gas-like body, slowly weakening its prey by poisoning it through the skin.

name: Gengar
flavorText: To steal the life of its target, it slips into the prey's shadow and silently waits for an opportunity.

name: Onix
flavorText: It rapidly bores through the ground at 50 mph by squirming and twisting its massive, rugged body.

name: Growlithe
flavorText: It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.

name: Kadabra
flavorText: This Pokémon's telekinesis is immensely powerful. To prepare for evolution, Kadabra stores up psychic energy in the star on its forehead.

name: Machop
flavorText: Always brimming with power, it passes time by lifting boulders. Doing so makes it even stronger.

name: Bellsprout
flavorText: Its bud looks like a human face. Because of the bud, it is rumored to be a type of legendary mandrake plant.

name: Tentacool
flavorText: This Pokémon is mostly made of water. A Tentacool out in the ocean is very hard to spot, because its body blends in with the sea.

name: Tentacruel
flavorText: Its 80 tentacles can stretch and shrink freely. Tentacruel ensnares prey in a net of spread-out tentacles, delivering venomous stings to its catch.

name: Golem ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Ponyta
flavorText: If you've been accepted by Ponyta, its burning mane is mysteriously no longer hot to the touch.

name: Slowpoke
flavorText: It is incredibly slow and dopey. It takes five seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.

name: Farfetch'd
flavorText: They use a plant stalk as a weapon, but not all of them use it in the same way. Several distinct styles of stalk fighting have been observed.

name: Doduo
flavorText: The brains in its two heads appear to communicate emotions to each other with a telepathic power.

name: Mankey
flavorText: It lives in groups in the treetops. If it loses sight of its group, it becomes infuriated by its loneliness.

name: Abra
flavorText: Abra can teleport in its sleep. Apparently the more deeply Abra sleeps, the farther its teleportations go.

name: Machoke
flavorText: Its formidable body never gets tired. It helps people by doing work such as the moving of heavy goods.

name: Machamp
flavorText: With four arms that react more quickly than it can think, it can execute many punches at once.

name: Weepinbell
flavorText: It spits out Poison Powder to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of Acid.

name: Graveler
flavorText: It travels by rolling down cliffs. If it falls into a river, it will explode with its last gasp.

name: Magnemite
flavorText: The electromagnetic waves emitted by the units at the sides of its head expel antigravity, which allows it to float.

name: Seel
flavorText: Thanks to its thick fat, cold seas don't bother it at all, but it gets tired pretty easily in warm waters.

name: Grimer
flavorText: Born from sludge, these Pokémon now gather in polluted places and increase the bacteria in their bodies.

name: Haunter
flavorText: It likes to lurk in the dark and tap shoulders with a gaseous hand. Its touch causes endless shuddering.

name: Golduck
flavorText: When it swims at full speed using its long, webbed limbs, its forehead somehow begins to glow.

name: Primeape
flavorText: It becomes wildly furious if it even senses someone looking at it. It chases anyone that meets its glare.

name: Poliwrath
flavorText: Poliwrath is skilled at both swimming and martial arts. It uses its well-trained arms to dish out powerful punches.

name: Alakazam ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Geodude
flavorText: It uses both hands to climb precipitous cliffs. People who see it in action have been known to take up bouldering.

name: Slowbro
flavorText: When a Slowpoke went hunting in the sea, its tail was bitten by a Shellder. That made it evolve into Slowbro.

name: Dewgong
flavorText: It sunbathes on the beach after meals. The rise in its body temperature helps its digestion.

name: Muk
flavorText: It's thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.

name: Shellder
flavorText: It is encased in a shell that is harder than diamond. Inside, however, it is surprisingly tender.

name: Cloyster
flavorText: Cloyster that live in seas with harsh tidal currents grow large, sharp spikes on their shells.

name: Hypno
flavorText: When it locks eyes with an enemy, it will use a mix of psi moves, such as Hypnosis and Confusion.

name: Cubone
flavorText: This Pokémon wears the skull of its deceased mother. Sometimes Cubone's dreams make it cry, but each tear Cubone sheds makes it stronger.

name: Marowak
flavorText: When this Pokémon evolved, the skull of its mother fused to it. Marowak's temperament also turned vicious at the same time.

name: Hitmonlee
flavorText: The legs freely contract and stretch. The stretchy legs allow it to hit a distant foe with a rising kick.

name: Hitmonchan
flavorText: Its punches slice the air. However, it seems to need a short break after fighting for three minutes.

name: Rhydon
flavorText: Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Kangaskhan ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Seadra
flavorText: Seadra's mouth is slender, but its suction power is strong. In an instant, Seadra can suck in food that's larger than the opening of its mouth.

name: Seaking
flavorText: Using its horn, it bores holes in riverbed boulders, making nests to prevent its eggs from washing away.

name: Staryu
flavorText: Fish Pokémon nibble at it, but Staryu isn't bothered. Its body regenerates quickly, even if part of it is completely torn off.

name: Magmar
flavorText: These Pokémon's bodies are constantly burning. Magmar are feared as one of the causes behind fires.

name: Tauros
flavorText: When it targets an enemy, it charges furiously while whipping its body with its long tails.

name: Flareon
flavorText: Inhaled air is carried to its flame sac, heated, and exhaled as fire that reaches over 3,000 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Omanyte
flavorText: This Pokémon is a member of an ancient, extinct species. Omanyte paddles through water with its 10 tentacles, looking like it's just drifting along.

name: Omastar
flavorText: Omastar's sharp fangs could crush rock, but the Pokémon can attack only the prey that come within reach of its tentacles.

name: Aerodactyl
flavorText: Aerodactyl's sawlike fangs can shred skin to tatters—even the skin of Steel-type Pokémon.

name: Snorlax
flavorText: This Pokémon's stomach is so strong, even eating moldy or rotten food will not affect it.

name: Voltorb
flavorText: It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.

name: Koffing
flavorText: Its body is full of poisonous gas. It floats into garbage dumps, seeking out the fumes of raw, rotting trash.

name: Rhyhorn
flavorText: It can remember only one thing at a time. Once it starts rushing, it forgets why it started.

name: Horsea
flavorText: They swim with dance-like motions and cause whirlpools to form. Horsea compete to see which of them can generate the biggest whirlpool.

name: Pinsir
flavorText: This Pokémon clamps its pincers down on its prey and then either splits the prey in half or flings it away.

name: Magikarp
flavorText: An underpowered, pathetic Pokémon. It may jump high on rare occasions but never more than seven feet.

name: Gyarados
flavorText: Once it appears, it goes on a rampage. It remains enraged until it demolishes everything around it.

name: Kabuto
flavorText: While some say this species has gone extinct, Kabuto sightings are apparently fairly common in some places.

name: Kabutops
flavorText: The cause behind the extinction of this species is unknown. Kabutops were aggressive Pokémon that inhabited warm seas.

name: Articuno
flavorText: This Pokémon can control ice at will. Articuno is said to live in snowy mountains riddled with permafrost.

name: Drowzee
flavorText: It remembers every dream it eats. It rarely eats the dreams of adults because children's are much tastier.

name: Kingler
flavorText: Its oversized claw is very powerful, but when it's not in battle, the claw just gets in the way.

name: Electrode
flavorText: The more energy it charges up, the faster it gets. But this also makes it more likely to explode.

name: Exeggutor
flavorText: When they work together, Exeggutor's three heads can put out powerful psychic energy. Cloudy days make this Pokémon sluggish.

name: Chansey
flavorText: This kindly Pokémon lays highly nutritious eggs and shares them with injured Pokémon or people.

name: Tangela
flavorText: Hidden beneath a tangle of vines that grows nonstop even if the vines are torn off, this Pokémon's true appearance remains a mystery.

name: Goldeen
flavorText: Its dorsal and pectoral fins are strongly developed like muscles. It can swim at a speed of five knots.

name: Mr. Mime
flavorText: It's known for its top-notch pantomime skills. It protects itself from all sorts of attacks by emitting auras from its fingers to create walls.

name: Jynx ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Electabuzz
flavorText: With the coming of a storm, many of these Pokémon will gather under tall trees and sit there waiting for lightning to strike.

name: Jolteon
flavorText: It concentrates the weak electric charges emitted by its cells and launches wicked lightning bolts.

name: Porygon
flavorText: In recent years, this species has been very helpful in cyberspace. These Pokémon will go around checking to make sure no suspicious data exists.

name: Krabby
flavorText: If it senses danger approaching, it cloaks itself with bubbles from its mouth so it will look bigger.

name: Exeggcute
flavorText: These Pokémon get nervous when they're not in a group of six. The minute even one member of the group goes missing, Exeggcute become cowardly.

name: Lickitung
flavorText: Bug Pokémon are Lickitung's main food source. This Pokémon paralyzes its prey with a lick from its long tongue, then swallows the prey whole.

name: Weezing
flavorText: Very rarely, a sudden mutation can result in two small Koffing twins becoming conjoined as a Weezing.

name: Starmie
flavorText: Starmie swims by spinning its body at high speed. As this Pokémon cruises through the ocean, it absorbs tiny plankton.

name: Scyther
flavorText: It slashes through grass with its sharp scythes, moving too fast for the human eye to track.

name: Lapras
flavorText: Crossing icy seas is no issue for this cold-resistant Pokémon. Its smooth skin is a little cool to the touch.

name: Ditto
flavorText: Its transformation ability is perfect. However, if made to laugh, it can't maintain its disguise.

name: Eevee
flavorText: Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.

name: Vaporeon
flavorText: It lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with a fin, which is often mistaken for a mermaid's.

name: Dragonair
flavorText: They say that if it emits an aura from its whole body, the weather will begin to change instantly.

name: Dragonite
flavorText: It is said that somewhere in the ocean lies an island where these gather. Only they live there.

name: Bill's Transfer
rules: ["Look at the top 8 cards of your deck. You may reveal any number of Pokémon you find there and put them into your hand. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.","You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn."]

name: Grabber

name: Caterpie
flavorText: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.

name: Mewtwo
flavorText: A Pokémon created by recombining Mew's genes. It's said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.

name: Charmander
flavorText: From the time it is born, a flame burns at the tip of its tail. Its life would end if the flame were to go out.

name: Antique Old Amber
rules: ["Play this card as if it were a 60-HP Basic Colorless Pokémon. This card can't be affected by any Special Conditions and can't retreat.  At any time during your turn, you may discard this card from play.","You may play any number of Item cards during your turn."]

name: Daisy's Help
rules: ["Draw 2 cards. Look at your face-down Prize cards.","You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn."]

name: Bulbasaur
flavorText: While it is young, it uses the nutrients that are stored in the seed on its back in order to grow.

name: Charmeleon
flavorText: If it becomes agitated during battle, it spouts intense flames, incinerating its surroundings.

name: Wartortle
flavorText: It cleverly controls its furry ears and tail to maintain its balance while swimming.

name: Zapdos ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Moltres
flavorText: There are stories of this Pokémon using its radiant, flame-cloaked wings to light up paths for those lost in the mountains.

name: Dratini
flavorText: It sheds many layers of skin as it grows larger. During this process, it is protected by a rapid waterfall.

name: Squirtle
flavorText: When it feels threatened, it draws its limbs inside its shell and sprays water from its mouth.

name: Machoke
flavorText: Its formidable body never gets tired. It helps people by doing work such as the moving of heavy goods.

name: Golem ex
rules: ["Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards."]

name: Mr. Mime

name: Omanyte
flavorText: This Pokémon is a member of an ancient, extinct species. Omanyte paddles through water with its 10 tentacles, looking like it's just drifting along.

name: Dragonair
flavorText: They say that if it emits an aura from its whole body, the weather will begin to change instantly.

name: Psyduck

name: Poliwhirl
flavorText: This Pokémon's sweat is a slimy mucus. When captured, Poliwhirl can slither from its enemies' grasp and escape.

name: Tangela
flavorText: Hidden beneath a tangle of vines that grows nonstop even if the vines are torn off, this Pokémon's true appearance remains a mystery.
